caption: This is one of my favorite!!! I love this place! Pad thai always on point extra spicy please!!! Costumer service gets 5 stars Also! Must try
The chicken pad thai is definitely above average.  The egg rolls not so much

I used to eat here all the time before the new owners bought it a few years ago. Now the portions are tiny, less friendly staff and the food is just mediocre. We found out where the old owner opened another restaurant and when we want excellent Thai food, we go there. It’s a drive but worth every minute and penny!
Good place for quality thai food. the food was amazing. this place has a nice design.
Thai Valley, Manee Thai, and this place are the best authentic Thai places on the northwest side of Chicago.
Pad kee mow is the best I’ve had in a while. Chicken pan fried pot stickers were perfect - seared, not deep fried like other places. Go here!

Love their food! Vegetables are always fresh, and service is excellent! My favorites are Panang Curry, Rama delight, Pad Thai, and Basil Chicken Tom Yum Soup. I appreciate that I can order extra veggies for my main dishes, I get more than 1 meal. Prices are very reasonable.
Nice location for delicious thai food. I can see why they have so many great reviews.

Small local place, kind people working, fast service and great food. Had shrimp rolls appetizer which was good choice, pad thai was amazing, sweet and sour, little bit spicy with extra soft noodles. We also had seafood special plate, which had a lot of different protein choices. Will be back forsure!
Bland food all around. Pad Thai and red curry have no flavor. Curry was very watery and unappetizing.
I order and recieved my meal I paid 285 cent for two shrimp in my fried rice

My favorite by far is the Thai Thai Restaurant chicken soup with flat rice noodles. On a cold winter day, it's refreshing due to the lime fishy flavor with the flavorful broth. Now this may not sound like a good description fish and chicken broth but it's familiar for my asian taste so it works for me.

WARNING: DO NOT GO HERE! I had troubles with my order and called the restaurant. Person who answered was rude. I got handed over to the manager or someone in a higher position, and he was worse. He was yelling at me on the phone and constantly interrupted me. He made it very hard for me to explain the situation without him yelling at me, saying things such as “what do you want me to do?”, “do you want me to pay for your mistake?”. The rudest staff I have ever spoken to.

I decided to try this place out and I was not disappointed! I ordered the Pad Thai and the Chicken Egg Rolls and it was delicious! This is my new go to! Support this small business and order directly from the restaurant's website! Thank me later! :)
First time in after driving past several times. I had the Pad Thai and the flavor was good, just a little light on the protein. I will try another dish soon.
Food was good if they actually gave me some. Got the bbq pork special it was 4 pieces of tiny pork over a pound of white rice. Mega fail
One of my preferred places to eat. very good location, clean, and awesome service. I recommend this place!

I'm having to leave this review because I have been coming to this location for the past 16 years maybe longer and the portions just seem to keep getting smaller and smaller.  And now I'm paying all this money for some Pad Thai which really all it is are some noodles with sauce a little bit of meat... the portion is so small now and the quality isn't quite what it used to be. I can make far better Pad Thai at home.  I remember getting a free almond cookie way back in the day. This place used to be wonderful.  I may come back in about a year to see if it's gone back at all.
2 year ago I was there with my family,today try the food again,  is so good like in the past, thank you!!!

I celebrated my nomination today in this delicious restaurant. Well we had a magnificent evening and the restaurant was certainly the reason for the strong evening. The team  helped in a very nice style, the cuisine was delicious and my guests were extremely  joyful. We shall absolutely come back again for more joyful events. thanks very much.
My go-to spot when i'm craving thai food
Tried this spot before with my friend and I am obsessed since then. I love the fantastic ambience and delicious dishes and drinks. 5 stars.

last night was our first time we visited this excellent restaurant. But It is absolutely not the last time. We enjoyed the evening very much with the good service, with the high quality  dishes and booze and with the comfortable charge. We will no doubt go back there in a short time.
yummy on my tummy
Great service, super tasty!✨✨
Food is soo delicious. 2 nd time here. Definitely will be back and bring my friends here.

caption: Amazing Thai food.Perfectly cooked !
Simple place with fresh ingredients and tasty

We enjoyed this place thoroughly. Didnt get a pic of the food cuz we gobbled it up! We came in for a late snack. We shared an order of veggie potstickers. Each crispy half-moon of dough was so flavorful, almost didnt need the soy sauce. Som tum was great. We will ask for peppers next time. He really liked his chicken satay. We will definitely return.
Small place but the food  its incredible  good  I love this place
Ordered door dash. Soup had a lot of canned mushrooms yuck. Small portions and pad thai noodles all broken. Asked for spicy.  Not. And barely no chicken. Wont order again
Cozy, casual Thai spot with friendly service and some of the freshest, most flavorful food I've ever had.
Just tripped over this place.  Yummy lunch Specials.  Great prices.  No Desserts.  I'll be back for Dinner!
Customer service was good the food was delicious especially the steak pepper some peanut butter sauce.  good I like their tea it's amazing.
Great food.
Great,great food small place good service friendly people
Good prices.Delicious food items.Great and friendly service. Would recommend to anyone looking for tasty Thai food.

Worst Thai basil and spring roll we have ever had!!!   It tasted like it was made by weight watchers. Who puts ground chicken in a Thai basil dish? And who wraps a soring roll in white bread. I have to add the Mongolian beef was flavorless. I will not be hitting up any fusion Asian places from now on. Authentic only. Ugh!
A small sit-down spot but comfortable. Great service and the food was delicious!
Excellent pineapple curry. Delicious papaya salad. Scrumptious noodle dishes 😋
Not only is the food bland and pretty flavorless, I just found metallic plastic in my pad Thai.....
Great food! Love the size of Curry ! 👍👌
Saturday night, college football, crazy busy. Service was good, food was great. Folks around us laughing, having fun. So glad we ate here
Excellent food for a pretty good price, friendly employees, and a chill atmosphere. The location is convenient as well.
Great tasty Thai food! Pineapple fried rice and pad Thai are my favorite!
One of my favorite restaurant's of all time
Very good.....

Small portions of average food with TERRIBLE service. They charged us for things we didn't order or receive and refused to refund the items, when complained they didn't care. They were just cool with openly stealing.
Delicious food and really good prices :P
We Love Thai Thai!  Used to order regularly when we lived in the city.  Went back with the family and the food was exactly as i remember it...fantastic!!! Don't change a thing.
Great price point
Awesome food. Must try. I regret not coming here earlier. I ate pepper steak and udon noodles in miso broth with tofu. Everything was delicious.
Hit or miss service but the consistent excellence of the food makes up for it.

I like all the dishes I’ve tried (soups, all appetizers, noodle dishes and chicken dishes) the Tom kha soup and pot stickers are my favorite! Only giving it four stars cuz the customer service is meh and they don’t have drink size options for their teas ( which are 50% ice)
Not my favorite and their lunch specials aren't as competitive as some of the other local Thai joints, but convenient and good for carry out.

I'm a long time customer but will no longer be taking my business here. Placed an order for delivery and it took nearly 2.5 hours to arrive. Called to check on it and was told 15 minutes, took another 45 after it. When the food finally arrived it was cold, and I hardly wanted to eat after the awful experience.
Good thai food for a good price. Usually quick delivery

This place isn't far from my house and kept passing by wondering if it was good. Walked by one day and it smelled great! Finally went there tn and was not disappointed. Their Tom Kah soup was probably one of the best I've actually had. The Pad Thai was goodand the lard nar that my parents ordered was the only complaint.( not enough flavor) shrimp rolls were good as well.  We'll def go again. The service was I'd say a B-. They def seem to be a more carry out place. You can tell that were they make most of the money. The inside is pretty small. About 5 tables.  Over all i liked the place and would go again.
this place is not of my go-to's for thai. i'll go out of my way for it. appetizers could all stand to go down $1, but it's good nonetheless.

This is my go-to Thai place.  Service is fast and the food is super good.  I love the Tom Kha soup, Chive Dumplings, Curry Fried Rice, and Pad See Ewe.  Seriously though, I haven't had anything bad off the menu.  Great for a quick take-out night, although the space is nice enough to eat in.
Ok

I can't say I was impressed with the long wait time or the bland and lackluster food I had at Thai Thai. Though the location is convenient, parking is difficult and better Thai can be found at nearby restaurants. I would recommend that Thai Thai learn from the quality of Ruk Sushi on Milwaukee, and Hands On Modern Thai & Sushi Bar on Irving Park Road.
Great food at a good price!!

Ordered egg rolls, crab rangoon, cashew chicken and mixed veggies on Grubhub, it took 1:35 minutes to arrive. It arrived cold and had to be microwaved. Terrible, gross, awful.  I really really hate this place. Really.
Delicious food, good price, friendly service

Delivery was less than expected. Food was hot and we'll garnished. Vegetables egg roll crispy and perfect light appetizer. Spicy chicken pa thai so delicious didn't want to share. Chicken fried rice delightful.
Wide selection
Happened upon this place by happy accident, food and service was great. Already recommended this place to friends.
It's dog food plan and simple. Don't not waste your money or time
Best Food in town. The only go to place for Thai food. Great service, and Amazing food.
Clean place, so much flavor, so good. Definitely  come back
Tasty and friendly place
This Thai Thai Restaurant is small but makes up on frendly staff and very good food.parking is limited on street.
They're awesome! Great selection, excellent food, great service!
We get carry out from here but now that they remodeled we might bring our own wine and dine in.  Incredibly nice people.
Great Thai food with good vegetarian and vegan options.
Good food.  Good portions.  No ambience.  Very small.  Bad exhaust system.  Definitely a take out only place.
Have it delivered. The food is pretty good and they deliver fast.  A reliable option for quick Thai food.

I've been to Thai Thai monthly for the past year and a bit. I've visited 20 times in the past year alone. Today, my pad thai was so oily that I barely ate it. Additionally, they fed my friend (we always go here together) who is a strict vegetarian of 18-yrs chicken on his dish instead of tofu. It was a fried dish, so he didn't notice until he bit it.  Upon notifying them of their mistake, they demonstrated awful service. The waitress and cook spoke loudly to each other (not in English, so don't know what they were saying) and LAUGHING loudly about this. It's a very serious matter - feeding a vegetarian meat is akin to giving them instant food poisoning.  They remade the dish, he barely ate it (we didn't take it to go) and they still charged us full price for the entire meal. They were extremely rude and unapologetic -- and as a result, they've lost 2 regular customers.
Stopped by for a visit. Nice location!
some say this is the best in the city... I'm not yet convinced but not staying away.
Great food!
Not really nasty bad,  but thier white rice has more flavor than everything else.
We love the food. It's always fresh! Good prices, great variety! Friendly people! Great service! Hasn't failed us yet!
Don't go here.
Good food, attentive service.  The layout is unusual, which I found a trifle uncomfortable.
To-go portions here are much smaller than if u eat in, and u dont get the soup. Half our order was wrong, and there was absolutely no flavor. Huge disappointment.
Very difficult to order online but great food stop here every time I'm in the area
Cheap and fairly tasty. Could use new tables and chairs. Service was fast.

I live close by and ate there a couple times, no complaints. It's been maybe 2 months but  days ago I ordered, take out. BBQ Pork and rice special. I swear that was about 50g of ham with BBQ sauce on top of white rice. It could not have been more than 2 thin ham slices , sliced in smaller squares to look more. I had a seaweed salad appetizer, there were more sliced cucumbers than seaweed and and one more entree and appetizer.  Seriously, for a Asian Restaurant your portions were smaller, but borderline normal. This time it was so ridiculous, I had to go out of my way to comment.  It's a shame Chang's Restaurant owners retired.

Fresh-tasting, solid delivery. A great alternative to heavy Chinese. The only thing I've ordered that I wasn't a fan of were the spring rolls -- they just weren't the type I was expecting. Everything else has been fab.

I ordered from here once via GrubHub, and specifically asked for no nuts seeds, or peanuts, because I'm allergic. Anyway, when my order came, it was covered in sesame seeds! Do not order from this place if you have allergies.
Best Thai place around!

This place has been around for quite a while and I must say that I like it since I keep coming back.  The food has been consistently good and its reasonably priced and come in fairly large portions, its also BYOB. Very quick and very warm, friendly service.  Be warned, this a no frills sort of restaurant, the place is sparsely decorated and there is no real flare to the food presentation, but the flavor makes up for it . I've always been a fan of the rangoon, the fried tofu, the pad thai wth tofu, and the Panang!  So if you want to get some great tasting warm food in a casual everyday sort of way, then go here. But if you're looking to impress someone while out on a date, this place might definitely hurt your chances.

Very quality thai food in a very non consuming building. I do feel as if the quality of the food or perhaps the experience has diminished under the new ownership. The food that struck me as home made and authentic, has lost some of its appeal. That being said, have not had a bad meal here.
Excellent, quick food. I had the lunch special and it was only $6.95 and more than I could eat in one sitting. Wonderful, I will be back soon!
Best pad thai in town
